      <p>Écrire en SQL : "Donne le nombre de films par notation (rating), uniquement pour les notations ayant plus de 200 films, triés par nombre décroissant."</p>
      <details class="answer">
        <summary><span class="summary-arrow">▶</span> Voir la correction</summary>
        <div class="answer-content">
          <table class="ans-table" style="margin-bottom:0.8rem">
            <tr><th>Clause</th><th>Rôle</th><th>⚠️ Piège</th></tr>
            <tr><td class="pk">SELECT rating, COUNT(*)</td><td class="attr">Afficher notation + nb films</td><td class="attr">—</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="pk">GROUP BY rating</td><td class="attr">Grouper par notation</td><td class="attr">—</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="pk" style="color:#c0392b">HAVING COUNT(*) &gt; 200</td><td class="attr">Filtrer les <strong>groupes</strong></td><td class="rule">⚠️ Pas WHERE ! WHERE filtre les lignes, HAVING filtre les groupes</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="pk">ORDER BY nb_films DESC</td><td class="attr">Trier décroissant</td><td class="attr">—</td></tr>
          </table>
          <div class="ans-code"><span class="c-kw">SELECT</span> rating, <span class="c-fn">COUNT</span>(*) <span class="c-kw">AS</span> nb_films
<span class="c-kw">FROM</span> film
<span class="c-kw">GROUP BY</span> rating
<span class="c-fn">HAVING</span> <span class="c-fn">COUNT</span>(*) &gt; <span class="c-num">200</span>
<span class="c-kw">ORDER BY</span> nb_films <span class="c-fn">DESC</span>;</div>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
